  <h1>Foam</h1>
  <div class="description">

   

    <p>The formation of foam along shorelines as usually a result of turbulent currents or wave action is a normal occurrence in waters high in dissolved organic matter, such as those found throughout the Ottawa River watershed.</p>

    <h2>Is it natural foam?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Colour:</strong> light tan or brown, but may be white</li>
      <li><strong>Smell:</strong> earthy, fishy or has fresh cut grass odor</li>
      <li><strong>Area:</strong> can occur over large areas and accumulate in large amounts, especially on windward shores, in coves and eddies</li>
      <li><strong>When:</strong> dissipates fairly quickly, except when agitated (as in high wind conditions)</li>
    </ul>

